usage: add_session.py [-h] --title TITLE [--commit COMMIT] [--summary SUMMARY]
                      [--content-file CONTENT_FILE] [--package PACKAGE]
                      [--no-commit] [--stdin]

Add a new session to journal file and update index.md

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --title TITLE         Session title
  --commit COMMIT       Comma-separated commit hashes
  --summary SUMMARY     Brief summary
  --content-file CONTENT_FILE
                        Path to file with detailed content
  --package PACKAGE     Package name tag (e.g., cli, docs-site)
  --no-commit           Skip auto-commit of workspace changes
  --stdin               Read extra content from stdin (explicit opt-in)
